WEBVTT

00:04.134 --> 00:07.433
<i>[ Chorus ]
 The Simpsons</i>

00:08.714 --> 00:10.014
BROTHER'S LITTLE HELPER

00:18.215 --> 00:20.115
<i>[ Bell Ringing ]</i>

00:24.989 --> 00:28.117
<i>[ Whistle Blowing ]</i>

00:30.527 --> 00:32.427
[ Beeping ]

00:38.168 --> 00:40.136
[Jazzy Solo ]

00:42.000 --> 00:48.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

01:00.157 --> 01:02.091
[ Beeping ]

01:02.192 --> 01:04.057
[ Tires Screeching ]

01:05.429 --> 01:07.420
D'oh!
[ Screams ]

01:23.147 --> 01:25.115
<i>[ Children Laughing ]</i>

01:26.550 --> 01:28.450
Whee!

01:28.552 --> 01:30.452
Catch!

01:30.554 --> 01:33.546
Principal Skinner, what would you say
is the most important firefighting tool?

01:33.657 --> 01:36.490
- Would you say it's prevention?
- Oh, absolutely, Lisa.

01:36.593 --> 01:39.084
- That and the sand bucket.
- What's that stuff?

01:39.196 --> 01:40.857
Why, this is retardant.

01:40.965 --> 01:43.399
[ Laughing ]
Sure is. And what's that?

01:43.500 --> 01:45.092
That's called a hose lengthener.

01:45.202 --> 01:46.863
[ Laughing ]
You need one.

01:46.971 --> 01:48.529
<i>- [ Skinner Groans ]
- What's this?</i>

01:48.639 --> 01:51.073
Just read the label.
It's a king-sized flamer!

01:51.175 --> 01:54.140
- [ Laughing Hysterically ]
- Bart, will you go bother someone else?

01:54.545 --> 01:56.740
<i>Look!
A fire... engine.</i>

01:56.847 --> 01:59.782
- Stop that!
- Help! Help! Fire... helmets.

01:59.883 --> 02:01.546
Can't you do something constructive?

02:01.752 --> 02:04.277
Sure, I can do
something destructive.

02:04.388 --> 02:05.488
[ Groaning ]

02:05.990 --> 02:08.458
Just say the word,
and I'll drive this hoe in his back!

02:08.959 --> 02:10.859
I can make it look like suicide.

02:10.961 --> 02:16.456
And I want a bike, and a monkey,
and a friend for the monkey-

02:16.567 --> 02:19.468
You're not gonna start
any fires, are you?

02:19.570 --> 02:21.902
At my house, we call 'em ''uh-ohs.''

02:22.006 --> 02:25.271
Hi, fire doggie.
Can you do any tricks?

02:25.376 --> 02:28.868
Tricks? That's rich.
He's so inbred, he can barely stand up.

02:28.979 --> 02:30.469
[ Whimpers ]

02:30.581 --> 02:32.481
Fire can be our servant...

02:32.583 --> 02:35.143
whether it's toasting s'mores
or raining down on Charlie.

02:35.252 --> 02:38.346
But it can turn not so nice,
as you'll see in this skit...

02:38.455 --> 02:40.787
by the Volunteer
Fire Department Players.

02:40.891 --> 02:43.325
<i>- [ Scattered Applause]
- [ Chuckles ]</i>

02:43.427 --> 02:46.760
- What a great pot party!
- Wasn't it, man?

02:46.864 --> 02:50.459
Now for a regular cigarette
to make the night complete.

02:50.567 --> 02:51.932
[ Coughs ]

02:52.036 --> 02:56.268
- Oh! Man, that's good.
- Mad Dog, I've been thinking.

02:56.373 --> 03:00.173
Maybe we should get another smoke detector
in case that one trips out on us.

03:00.277 --> 03:02.575
[ Chuckling ]
Why bother, baby?

03:02.679 --> 03:04.909
One smoke detector's enough
for Mad Dog.

03:05.015 --> 03:07.040
Now, let's hit the sack.

03:09.586 --> 03:12.714
[ Exhales, Snores ]

03:12.823 --> 03:15.815
Whoa! Check it out!
Mad Dog's on fire!

03:15.926 --> 03:17.985
Stop, drop and roll, man!

03:18.095 --> 03:20.620
[ Chuckling ]
That's for Clydes, baby.

03:20.731 --> 03:24.599
- A little fire can't hurt you.
- But Mad Dog was wrong.

03:24.701 --> 03:26.464
The fire burned through the night...

03:26.570 --> 03:28.800
and cost him the use of his pants.

03:28.906 --> 03:30.669
Which just goes to show you- Huh?

03:30.774 --> 03:32.674
[ Gasps ]
Sorry to break character...

03:32.776 --> 03:35.711
- but these stunt pants are gettin' pretty toasty!
- Roll, Neddie! Roll!

03:35.813 --> 03:38.111
[ Laughter]

03:38.215 --> 03:40.149
It's not workin'!
It just spreads the flame!

03:40.250 --> 03:42.241
Get the fire hose.
Get the fire hose!

03:45.656 --> 03:47.556
What's it doing in the gymnasium?

03:47.658 --> 03:50.320
Yee-haw!

03:50.427 --> 03:52.987
Bart, have you lost your-
[ Yells ]

03:53.097 --> 03:55.031
[ Both Yelling ]

03:55.132 --> 03:57.293
[ Yelling ]

04:00.604 --> 04:02.504
[ Groans, Sputters ]

04:04.842 --> 04:06.707
[ Laughing Hysterically ]

04:06.810 --> 04:10.268
- Bart Simpson!
- You've really done it this time.

04:10.380 --> 04:12.280
Yeah. It all kind of came together.

04:14.785 --> 04:17.583
[ Squeaking ]

04:17.688 --> 04:20.851
[ Grunting ]

04:20.958 --> 04:22.858
[ Sighs ]

04:22.960 --> 04:25.360
[ Grunts ]
Thank you for coming.

04:25.462 --> 04:27.123
Thank you for getting me
out of work.

04:27.231 --> 04:29.131
I'll be blunt.
Bart's latest escapade...

04:29.233 --> 04:31.201
goes far beyond the realm
of the high jink.

04:31.301 --> 04:34.759
There. Now the floor
is as good as new.

04:36.607 --> 04:39.633
[ Groans ]
My sport goggles!

04:39.743 --> 04:44.146
Your son is a ravenous demon, relentlessly
gnawing at all that's good and true.

04:44.248 --> 04:46.011
Yeah, he's something else, all right.

04:46.116 --> 04:49.813
But worst of all, he drags down
the grades of anyone who sits near him.

04:49.920 --> 04:52.821
<i>-Just look at this pattern.
- [ Homer] Hey, that looks like Bart.</i>

04:52.923 --> 04:58.725
<i>And turning to the 3-D map,
we see an unmistakable cone of ignorance.</i>

04:58.829 --> 05:00.626
Put it away!
Put it away!

05:00.731 --> 05:02.790
Very well.
But there's no escaping the truth.

05:02.900 --> 05:05.698
Bart has a classic case
of attention deficit disorder.

05:05.802 --> 05:07.565
You mean like John Leguizamo?

05:07.671 --> 05:09.571
How should I know?
The point is...

05:09.673 --> 05:12.540
A.D.D. makes children restless
and easily distracted.

05:12.643 --> 05:15.476
- Hi, Marge. It's me- Homer.
- [ Clears Throat ]

05:15.579 --> 05:18.173
- What? Time to go?
- Please, Mr. Simpson.

05:18.282 --> 05:20.307
- I'm afraid I'll have to expel your son-
- [ Gasps ]

05:20.417 --> 05:23.818
unless you're willing to try a radical,
untested, potentially dangerous-

05:23.921 --> 05:27.186
- Candy bar?
- No! It's a new drug called Focusyn.

05:27.291 --> 05:30.624
A drug? I know Bart
can be rambunctious...

05:30.727 --> 05:33.924
<i>- but he's not some hyperactive monster.
- [ Bart ] Gimme an ''F''!</i>

05:34.031 --> 05:35.726
- [ Gasps ] Good Lord!
- Gimme an ''art''!

05:35.832 --> 05:37.561
<i>- He's gotten into the pep closet.
- What's that spell?</i>

05:37.668 --> 05:41.195
I'd say he's coming out of the pep closet.
[ Chuckles ]

05:46.944 --> 05:49.811
I don't wanna pump
my little boy full of drugs.

05:49.913 --> 05:53.314
- Yeah, yeah, we get a lot of that.
- But then they see our results.

05:53.417 --> 05:56.545
These are normal guinea pigs
running around like idiots.

05:56.653 --> 05:59.679
- [ All Squealing ]
- Now I'll give them some Focusyn.

06:04.795 --> 06:08.595
[ Gasps ]
That's amazing... and darling.

06:08.699 --> 06:13.159
- Check this out.
- [ Soft Squealing ]

06:13.270 --> 06:15.670
- They become your slaves.
- Yes.

06:15.772 --> 06:19.173
But it's not about slavery.
It's about helping kids concentrate.

06:19.276 --> 06:22.211
<i>This pill reduces
class clownism 44%..</i>

06:22.312 --> 06:24.303
<i>With 60%. less sass mouth.</i>

06:24.414 --> 06:27.440
- The only thing more effective is regular exercise.
- [ Shudders ]

06:27.551 --> 06:30.884
<i>- ?? [ Video Game]
- [ Grunting ]</i>

06:30.988 --> 06:32.956
- Shred it! Shred it!
- [ Indistinct Shouting ]

06:33.056 --> 06:35.320
Extra gloves. Extra gloves.
Mushroom bonus. Reload.

06:35.425 --> 06:38.326
[ Groans ]
How will we get Bart to take these?

06:38.428 --> 06:40.396
It's all about trust, honey.

06:42.366 --> 06:45.961
Ow!
Knock it off!.

06:46.069 --> 06:49.266
Homer, we agreed we'd discuss
the medication with Bart.

06:49.373 --> 06:54.811
- Medication?
- Some special helpers that'll make you a good boy.

06:54.911 --> 06:57.709
- I don't wanna take drugs.
- Sure you do.

06:57.814 --> 06:59.873
All your favorite stars
have used drugs.

06:59.983 --> 07:01.883
Brett Butler, Tim Allen-

07:01.985 --> 07:03.816
- Tommy Lee.
- Andy Dick.

07:03.920 --> 07:06.320
- He's just flamboyant.
- Yeah, and I'm a size four.

07:06.423 --> 07:08.755
Dad, I admit I have some problems...

07:08.859 --> 07:10.759
but drugs aren't the answer.

07:10.861 --> 07:13.193
- Why, you little-
- [ Screaming ]

07:14.398 --> 07:17.561
Son, let's forget
all about that drug thing.

07:17.668 --> 07:20.899
Why don't you just come down
and have some taffy?

07:21.004 --> 07:22.904
- Nice try, Homer.
-Just take one bite.

07:23.006 --> 07:26.806
<i>If you're not 100%. different-
Ow! Geez, what's the big deal?</i>

07:26.910 --> 07:29.310
Look, I'll even eat some.

07:29.413 --> 07:31.313
Now- Hmm?

07:31.415 --> 07:33.679
[ Gibberish ]

07:37.387 --> 07:40.083
Does Mr. Simpson
have a demon, Daddy?

07:40.190 --> 07:43.785
- Looks like it. Run and get Daddy's exorcism tongs.
- [ Together] Yea!

07:43.894 --> 07:45.919
[ Gibberish Continues ]

07:46.029 --> 07:49.556
Honey, if you don't wanna
take the medicine, we won't force you.

07:49.666 --> 07:50.894
Really?

07:53.236 --> 07:56.637
Yes, I just thought you might
love me enough to let me help you.

07:58.575 --> 08:00.873
Oh, Mom!

08:00.977 --> 08:03.878
All right.
I'll do it for you.

08:03.980 --> 08:06.175
- [ Gulps ]
- Way to guilt him, Marge.

08:06.283 --> 08:08.774
It's what I do.

08:08.885 --> 08:10.978
[ Gibberish ]

08:17.728 --> 08:19.662
Good morning, honey.
Mmm!

08:19.763 --> 08:21.788
How's my special little guy?

08:21.898 --> 08:24.298
- I'm having some side effects from the dope.
- It's not dope!

08:24.401 --> 08:26.301
It's something
to help you concentrate.

08:26.403 --> 08:29.429
All I know is my testicles
won't fit in my underwear.

08:29.539 --> 08:31.632
<i>Bart, get those oranges out of there.</i>

08:31.742 --> 08:34.472
- [ Laughing ]
- Back in the lunches you go.

08:34.578 --> 08:36.010
Ew, Mom!

08:36.113 --> 08:37.876
- Oh, grow up.
- Yeah.

08:40.150 --> 08:42.049
I have to take these stupid pills
twice a day.

08:42.152 --> 08:44.052
I'll trade you a Claritin for one.

08:44.154 --> 08:46.247
- Claritin-D?
- Nah.

08:46.356 --> 08:48.881
- Can't help you.
- I take hormones to lower my voice.

08:48.992 --> 08:52.553
Now all I wanna do is fight.
What are you lookin' at?

08:52.662 --> 08:55.654
You think you got it bad?
I gotta wear a shock collar.

08:55.766 --> 08:57.666
- Ooh!
- That's rough.

08:57.768 --> 08:59.565
- [ Screams ]
- What was that for?

08:59.669 --> 09:01.694
I thought about a girl I like.

09:01.805 --> 09:05.400
All right, class, who would like to read
''The Daffodils'' by Wordsworth?

09:05.509 --> 09:08.945
- I'll do it.
- No, thank you, Mr. Wisenheimer. Sherri?

09:09.045 --> 09:11.479
''I wandered lonely as a cloud...

09:11.581 --> 09:13.549
that floats on high
o'er vales and hills''-

09:13.650 --> 09:15.550
Hey, look at those dogs going at it!

09:15.652 --> 09:17.483
- I wanna see 'em! I wanna see 'em!
- [ Voices Overlapping ]

09:17.587 --> 09:19.418
Fightin' over a fan belt.

09:19.523 --> 09:21.855
Dogs are outstanding.

09:21.958 --> 09:25.792
All right, people, we've all seen
the dogs now, so- [ Gasps ]

09:25.896 --> 09:27.557
- What?
- You're still in your seat.

09:27.664 --> 09:29.859
Well, it's not like
I never saw a dog before.

09:29.966 --> 09:31.866
[ Thinking ]
That doesn't sound like me.

09:31.968 --> 09:33.868
Could it be the drug kicking in?

09:33.970 --> 09:37.133
I am feeling an urge
to straighten up and fly right.

09:37.240 --> 09:40.300
Come on, people.
This poetry isn't gonna appreciate itself.

09:40.410 --> 09:42.241
[ Applause On TV]

09:42.345 --> 09:44.939
What a lovely day in the park.

09:45.048 --> 09:47.949
A perfect place to meet a lady.

09:51.221 --> 09:55.487
Ooh, la, la!
It's Sideshow Melanie!

09:55.592 --> 09:57.093
- [ Laughter]
- Hey, what's goin' on?

09:57.093 --> 09:59.084
- [ Laughter]
- Hey, what's goin' on?

09:59.196 --> 10:01.391
Hey, this thing's cuttin' off my air!

10:03.633 --> 10:06.727
[ Grunting ]
Oh!

10:06.837 --> 10:10.000
<i>What are you doing to me?
I said start it at 60 r.p.m....</i>

10:10.106 --> 10:12.597
then move it up to 100
on the skirt blow!

10:12.709 --> 10:15.803
<i>- Sorry, Krusty, I choked.
- You choked? You choked?</i>

10:15.912 --> 10:19.541
Bart! Bart!
Krusty just fired his associate producer.

10:19.649 --> 10:22.743
- I'm reading.
- No way.

10:22.853 --> 10:25.947
<i>''The Seven Habits of
Highly Effective Pre-Teens''?</i>

10:26.056 --> 10:29.184
Is this all because of the-
[ Gulps, Groans ]

10:29.292 --> 10:33.160
<i>Joke if you will, but did you know
most people use 10%.
 of their brains?</i>

10:33.263 --> 10:35.254
<i>I am now one of them.</i>

10:35.365 --> 10:37.265
Before, my energy
was all over the place.

10:37.367 --> 10:39.528
Now, it's concentrated
like a laser beam.

10:39.636 --> 10:42.571
Well, this has been terrific.
Let's do it again sometime.

10:42.672 --> 10:45.402
- Are you standing up to get me to leave?
- It's from the book.

10:45.509 --> 10:47.602
Hey, I'm not a time burglar.

10:47.711 --> 10:50.179
''Memo to self: Lock door.''

10:50.280 --> 10:53.340
All right, I'll go.
You don't have to be a jerk about it.

10:53.450 --> 10:57.113
- ''Memo to self: Shut up, Lisa.''
- [ Shouts ]

11:00.123 --> 11:04.219
Hmm. ''Thank you in advance
for a world-class meal.

11:04.327 --> 11:08.696
You're an inspiration to our entire
organization. Thank you again. Bart.''

11:08.798 --> 11:11.096
Oh, what a lovely gesture.

11:11.201 --> 11:14.500
Cost of paper: five cents.
A mother's love: priceless.

11:14.604 --> 11:16.003
- Aw.
- Do I get a card?

11:16.106 --> 11:18.734
<i>No, but here's a book called
Chicken Soup for the Loser...</i>

11:18.842 --> 11:21.208
that gave Bill Buckner the courage
to open a chain of laundromats.

11:21.311 --> 11:24.803
Hmm. My career
has kind of lost momentum.

11:24.915 --> 11:26.940
I think it's the bright blue pants.

11:27.050 --> 11:29.075
I mean, you're not on a golf course.

11:29.185 --> 11:31.949
Well, I have been thinking
about making them into cutoffs.

11:33.957 --> 11:35.515
I tell you, the kid's a wonder.

11:35.625 --> 11:40.255
He organized all the lawsuits
against me into one class action.

11:40.363 --> 11:43.230
- That's gonna save all kinds of travel time.
- You know it.

11:43.333 --> 11:46.769
Plus, he gave me this appointment dealy.
It's got my whole week in there.

11:46.870 --> 11:48.030
<i>- [ Lenny Whistles ]
- [ Carl ] Sweet.</i>

11:48.138 --> 11:50.436
This thing'll do anything.
Watch.

11:50.540 --> 11:52.440
I'll ask it how many leagues
in a furlong.

11:52.542 --> 11:55.705
No, wait. I'll make it say,
''What's a-matter, you?'' in Turkish.

11:55.812 --> 11:58.212
- [ Computerized Voice
Speaking Foreign Language ]
- And look at this!

11:58.315 --> 12:01.978
- A cheese grater!
- Man, technology's amazing.

12:02.085 --> 12:04.519
A guy could do great things
with a gadget like that.

12:04.621 --> 12:06.521
Well, if you want one,
they sell 'em at-

12:06.623 --> 12:09.057
Yeah, a guy could do great things.
[ Slurping ]

12:12.929 --> 12:15.261
<i>The boy's still studying?</i>

12:15.365 --> 12:19.426
Can you believe it?
And he's even tutoring a little Navajo boy.

12:19.536 --> 12:22.164
And why did Humpty Dumpty
have a great fall?

12:22.272 --> 12:25.173
Because he took his eyes
off the prize?

12:25.275 --> 12:27.743
That's right.
You stay on the ball, you stay on the wall.

12:27.844 --> 12:29.903
He's gone from goofus to gallant.

12:30.013 --> 12:34.040
And we owe it all
to mind-bending pills.

12:34.150 --> 12:36.209
Bart's so well-behaved now.

12:36.319 --> 12:38.412
Maybe you and I
can have a night out.

12:38.521 --> 12:42.048
Ooh! Let's go to the water park!
My 10-year ban ended yesterday.

12:42.158 --> 12:46.356
I was thinking of something
a little more... adult.

12:46.463 --> 12:49.398
- [ Whispering ]
- Oh, Marge!

12:49.499 --> 12:51.933
And then afterwards-
[ Whispering Continues ]

12:52.035 --> 12:54.731
[ Giggles ]
Really? With butterscotch on it?

12:54.838 --> 12:56.738
I think you misheard me.

12:59.309 --> 13:02.870
You've got more talent than any dancer I've
ever seen, and you're throwing it all away!

13:02.979 --> 13:05.641
Screw you!
Screw everybody!

13:05.749 --> 13:09.412
All right, girls, tops off.
It's showtime!

13:09.519 --> 13:12.181
[ Moans ]
Marge, this is the greatest gift...

13:12.288 --> 13:14.188
any wife has ever given her husband.

13:14.290 --> 13:16.884
I thought you'd like it.
And I'm enjoying the friendship...

13:16.993 --> 13:19.723
- between showgirl and that seamstress.
- Pipe down!

13:19.829 --> 13:22.855
- Yes. Hush up.
- You hush up!
- Quiet, everybody!

13:22.966 --> 13:25.901
Shut up, or I'll pound all of ya!
[ Yells ]

13:27.137 --> 13:30.072
That was fun!
We have to get out more often.

13:30.173 --> 13:34.234
I heard about a new bar where men
dance with men. Doesn't that sound adorable?

13:34.344 --> 13:36.471
Well, sure, if it's true.

13:36.579 --> 13:38.479
[ Gasps ]
Is that Lisa?

13:42.686 --> 13:45.314
I'm so glad you're here.
Bart's really acting funny.

13:45.422 --> 13:47.913
- RayJ. funny, or O.J. funny?
- You'll see.

13:48.024 --> 13:51.824
<i>- [ Bart Muttering Incoherently ]
Gotta get it done.
- Bart? Honey?</i>

13:51.928 --> 13:55.557
<i>Gotta finish.
[ Grunting ]</i>

13:55.665 --> 13:57.565
<i>- Close the door.
- [ Door Closes ]</i>

13:57.667 --> 13:59.692
You're probably wondering
about the coat hangers.

13:59.803 --> 14:01.703
They're to block the satellite
that's been spying on me.

14:01.805 --> 14:03.705
Okay.

14:03.807 --> 14:06.173
It can read your electronic
organizer from space.

14:06.276 --> 14:08.744
- Even mine?
- [ Grunting ]

14:08.845 --> 14:10.642
Hey, I had Lenny's name on that!

14:10.747 --> 14:12.647
<i>They have it now.</i>

14:12.749 --> 14:14.876
<i>And who are they, exactly?</i>

14:14.984 --> 14:16.918
Who else?
Major League Baseball.

14:17.020 --> 14:20.478
Marge, I think Bart's gone crazy.

14:20.590 --> 14:23.559
- Oh, Bart, what's happened to you?
- Nothing yet.

14:23.660 --> 14:27.187
But the time draws near.
Now, let's get those fillings out of you!

14:27.297 --> 14:30.789
- [ Screaming ]
- Hey, you found my needle-nose pliers.

14:33.670 --> 14:37.470
I understand the electrodes,
but why does he have to be on a treadmill?

14:37.574 --> 14:40.475
- Oh, that was his idea. He said he felt fat.
- Oh.

14:40.577 --> 14:42.602
You said he was concerned
about satellites?

14:42.712 --> 14:45.306
- And their beams.
- Any other strange behavior?

14:45.415 --> 14:47.508
He quit blinking.
He says that's when they get you.

14:47.617 --> 14:49.517
I had a feeling this might happen.

14:49.619 --> 14:51.610
This carboxyl group
sometimes causes problems.

14:51.721 --> 14:54.986
After we trusted you!
[ Grunting ]

14:55.091 --> 14:58.026
- I think we should take him off the drug.
- Whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa!

14:58.128 --> 15:00.460
You can't just go ''off' Focusyn.

15:00.563 --> 15:03.225
But we can ease Bart onto
one of its sister drugs...

15:03.333 --> 15:06.268
like chlorhexinol, and augment that
with some phenolbutamine.

15:06.369 --> 15:10.863
- Hmm, and maybe some cyclobenzanone?
- That's a great idea!

15:10.974 --> 15:13.772
[ Grunts ]
No! You can't take my Focusyn.

15:13.877 --> 15:16.846
I need every brain cell blazing
to outwit my invisible enemies.

15:16.946 --> 15:19.540
I know you love Focusyn, son,
but in time...

15:19.649 --> 15:23.050
you'll get just as attached
to these three amigos.

15:23.153 --> 15:25.178
No!

15:28.992 --> 15:31.017
[ Gasps ]

15:32.695 --> 15:36.597
Uh-oh! Somebody's
gonna have a tummy ache.

15:36.699 --> 15:39.190
Stop him!
He's whacked out of his gourd!

15:39.302 --> 15:41.998
Don't worry.
We have a procedure for these situations.

15:46.709 --> 15:50.668
- Ahh!
- Hey, there was just air in mine.

15:50.780 --> 15:52.748
[ Groaning ]

15:56.352 --> 15:59.651
And I'm really worried, Chief.
There's no telling what he might do.

15:59.756 --> 16:02.953
Okay, so you say your son
is towheaded, button nose...

16:03.059 --> 16:05.721
mischievous smile,
and maybe armed with a slingshot?

16:05.829 --> 16:08.457
Got it.
We'll find him, ma'am.

16:08.565 --> 16:11.830
<i>[ Snickers ] Looks like the kid
who roughed up the Wilson widow.</i>

16:11.935 --> 16:15.996
Oh, my little guy's out there
in the hot sun without his sombrero.

16:16.105 --> 16:18.539
We should've paid more attention
to these side effects.

16:18.641 --> 16:22.099
It's all here-
erratic behaviour, paranoia, diarrhea-

16:22.212 --> 16:23.645
I don't think he has diarrhea.

16:23.746 --> 16:26.579
But how do we know, Marge?
How do we know?

16:32.658 --> 16:35.658
I can't believe that Sarge said 
we're the worst bunch he's ever seen

16:36.059 --> 16:38.926
- See, I have to believe he's
seen worse bunches than us.
- But he said-

16:39.028 --> 16:41.360
I know what he said.
He was just trying to motivate us.

16:41.464 --> 16:45.423
- Well, it ruined the whole hike.
- [ Sinister Chuckle ]

16:45.535 --> 16:48.060
[ Demented Laughter]

16:48.171 --> 16:51.937
-Do you think Alex would mind if I asked Janet out?
-They're married, idiot!

16:52.041 --> 16:54.202
Why'd you have to yell?
You ruined the whole shower.

16:55.945 --> 17:00.143
So I gave up tap for jazz, and I've
never regretted it. And here's why.

17:00.250 --> 17:03.947
- Homer, you're supposed to be hunting for Bart.
- I'm on top of it.

17:06.521 --> 17:09.082
[ Groans ]
My sweet baby.

17:09.192 --> 17:11.752
He must feel so helpless and scared.

17:13.429 --> 17:16.626
 Don't stop thinking about tomorrow 

17:16.733 --> 17:19.702
Don't stop, it'll soon be here
- [ Screaming ]

17:19.801 --> 17:21.098
[ All Screaming ]

17:21.204 --> 17:23.104
Smithers, we're at war!

17:23.205 --> 17:25.606
- I'll begin profiteering, sir.
- And hoarding.

17:25.708 --> 17:28.369
Leave it to the Democrats
to let the Spaniards back in the pantry.

17:33.116 --> 17:36.347
Egad! A maniac cutting
a swath of destruction!

17:36.452 --> 17:39.012
This is a job for
the Green Lantern, Thundra...

17:39.122 --> 17:42.114
or possibly... Ghost Rider.

17:42.225 --> 17:44.352
- What about Superman?
- Oh, please.

17:47.764 --> 17:49.959
What the- Hmm?

17:50.066 --> 17:52.762
Come on! Get out!
Noodles, Seesaw, Oopsie...

17:52.869 --> 17:55.531
Lobsweat, Hoohah,Jitters,
Sir Wide Bottom!

17:55.638 --> 17:57.503
Oh. I'm stuck.

17:57.607 --> 17:59.370
- Easy, boys. My bum.
- [ All Straining ]

18:03.313 --> 18:05.372
I'm sure I'm alive, but why?

18:05.481 --> 18:08.279
[ Screaming ]

18:08.384 --> 18:10.477
[ Cheering ]

18:10.586 --> 18:13.987
You've raised the bar for all of us,
Simpson, and I thank you.

18:14.090 --> 18:16.524
- Wow. Praise from Caesar.
- Huh?

18:16.626 --> 18:19.117
[ Siren Wailing ]

18:19.228 --> 18:22.664
- Shoot the tires out, Lou.
- Uh, it's a tank, Chief.

18:22.765 --> 18:25.359
You know what?
I'm gettin' real tired of your excuses.

18:25.468 --> 18:27.732
[ Chattering ]

18:31.607 --> 18:34.667
What a day! First, the drinking fountain
squirts me, and now this.

18:42.285 --> 18:44.412
My God, is she brave...

18:44.520 --> 18:47.045
standing up to that
freaked-out junkie.

18:47.156 --> 18:49.215
Dad, that junkie is your son.

18:49.325 --> 18:51.225
Why don't you just tell everybody?

18:51.327 --> 18:52.851
Hey, Mom.
Thanks for coming out.

18:52.962 --> 18:55.590
Oh, thank you for stopping the tank.

18:55.698 --> 18:57.689
- It ran out of gas.
- Oh.

18:57.800 --> 18:59.529
- So, Bart-
- Question.

18:59.635 --> 19:02.695
How about getting
out of the tank, huh?

19:02.805 --> 19:06.502
Maybe stopping your rampage, huh?
We could go to Krusty Burger.

19:06.609 --> 19:08.270
- Okay, sure.
- Whew!

19:08.378 --> 19:11.609
- Right after I blow up one thing.
- [ Groans ]

19:15.418 --> 19:17.318
[ Gasps ]
Good Lord! He's going to fire!

19:17.420 --> 19:20.583
All right!
Scud the school, dude!

19:20.690 --> 19:22.783
No, stop.
Think of the children.

19:24.727 --> 19:28.925
[ All Gasping ]

19:29.032 --> 19:32.331
Not the church!
Jesus lives there!

19:34.470 --> 19:36.836
The frame store?
You monster!

19:39.242 --> 19:42.268
Not the sky!
That's where clouds are born!

19:46.349 --> 19:48.317
[ All Gasping ]

19:50.253 --> 19:52.813
[ Siren Wailing ]

19:52.922 --> 19:55.356
A satellite?
What do we do? What do we do?

19:55.458 --> 19:57.983
''Discotheques, frat houses, Malibu''-

19:58.094 --> 19:59.994
Nothing about satellite fires.

20:00.096 --> 20:03.031
Let's just spray it with water already.

20:03.132 --> 20:06.795
That's the end of your loony tune,
Drugs Bunny.

20:06.903 --> 20:09.371
You're under arrest
for astro-vandalism.

20:09.472 --> 20:12.134
And may God help you if that thing
carried the Spice Channel!

20:14.510 --> 20:16.171
''Major League Baseball''?

20:16.279 --> 20:18.679
I told you they were
monitoring my activities.

20:18.781 --> 20:22.148
He's right!
This thing's got info on everybody.

20:22.251 --> 20:25.482
Addresses, credit ratings,
what size baseball hat they wear.

20:25.588 --> 20:28.022
[ Computerized Voice ]
Surveillance beam disabled.

20:28.124 --> 20:31.685
Market research shutting down.
Doesn't that beat all?

20:33.596 --> 20:36.963
- Hi, folks. I'm Mark McGwire.
- [ All Gasping ]

20:37.066 --> 20:39.466
Big Mac himself.
Who'd have thunk it?

20:39.569 --> 20:43.061
Young Bart here was right. We are spying
on you pretty much around the clock.

20:43.172 --> 20:46.733
- But why, Mr. McGwire?
- Do you wanna know the terrifying truth...

20:46.843 --> 20:49.038
or do you wanna see me
sock a few dingers?

20:49.145 --> 20:52.171
[ All ]
Dingers! Dingers!

20:52.281 --> 20:54.272
[ All ]
Ooh!

20:54.383 --> 20:56.351
Yoink!

21:01.691 --> 21:03.522
It's good to have the old Bart back.

21:03.626 --> 21:06.789
Plus, you exposed the disturbing
unreadiness of today's army.

21:06.896 --> 21:10.559
Oh, honey, I'm so sorry we sent you
on that psychotropic hayride.

21:10.666 --> 21:12.691
At least I got to see
some cool colors.

21:12.802 --> 21:15.794
And Mark McGwire gave you
an autographed bat.

21:15.905 --> 21:18.339
Why is the zero made out of glass?

21:18.441 --> 21:21.569
Who cares?
That man can really slug.

21:21.677 --> 21:24.908
Well, I'm not giving my baby
any more dangerous drugs.

21:25.014 --> 21:27.380
From now on,
it's nothing but fresh air...

21:27.483 --> 21:30.509
lots of hugs
and good old-fashioned Ritalin.

21:30.620 --> 21:33.020
You said a mouthful.

21:33.122 --> 21:36.387
 When I can't stop fiddlin'
I just takes me Ritalin 

21:36.492 --> 21:40.326
 I'm poppin' and sailin', man 
- [ Toots Twice ]

22:26.008 --> 22:27.908
- [ Murmuring ]
- Shh!

22:28.010 --> 22:30.410
<i>[ Man ] Oh, why'd you have to shush?
You ruined the whole show!</i>

